         <div type="translation">
            <ab>MH 1430, recto: (1) Paeris, son of Pamonthes, son ofPetosiris, has paid to the bank (2) of the northern houses for the bath (tax) of year 11 in Jeme, (3) 1 kite. Likewise, for silver of dike, 1 stater, 1/2 kite, 3 1/2 obols / 1 kite, 4 1/2 obols / 1 stater, (4) 1/2 kite, 3 1/2 obols again. Written in year 11, Mesore 11. Likewise, in year 12, Thoth (5) 12, 1/2 kite, 1/2 obol / 4 1/2 obols / 1/2 kite, 1/2 obol again. likewise, [for] apomoira, (6) 1/2 kite, 4 obols / 5 obols / 1/2 kite, 4 obols again.</ab>
         </div>
